<br>
For you to say that we are 'now' changing the rotation implies that we are lieing and/or have some hidden agenda to screw people over.  The fact is that the guilds who participated in the Dozekar rotation have *always* done it this way.  Because the 'rules' weren't posted until now does not imply that the rules have suddenly changed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As i understand it if the RTA is only for links and stuff, then how was a vote taken place for the rotation schedule? If these rules are being changed and Mobs that smaller guilds can kill are being taken away from them, then how is this rotation what the community wants, unless they voted on it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Rotation schedules are 'voted' on at the time someone is added to the rotation.  For instance, BotS kills Arch Lich (AL).  BotS is the only guild killing AL for a while.  No issues yet.  Tindi Losi then kills AL.  BotS and Tindi agree to a rotation, taking turns on AL, 'standard' rotation rules.  NB is bored one night so they decide to kill AL.  NB announces that they have killed AL and want into the rotation.  Since NB killed AL on what was actually BotS's (I think this was actually the case) turn, then BotS will go after them so now it is NB, BotS, Tindi in that order.  This is accepted with no contest by all three guilds involved (the community for the AL rotation).<br>
<br>
Again, your are accusing multiple guilds of changing the rotation rules on the fly and lieing about it to suit their own ends.  In most cases, the Dozekar rotation (in this case) is almost 'out of style' for the guilds involved.  Why would they want to do this?<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We have to camp quest Mobs all the time, but they are not on the Rotation. I think the rotation is great and I'm all for it, but please don't change the rules and expect the smaller guilds who can kill the Nameds and have been, not to be upset.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again, you are assuming that the rules were changed in the last day or two.  They were not changed, they were finally posted in a public forum so that you could see them.  Had you asked NB or Tindi 6 months ago, it would have been the same... even a year ago it would have been the same.  The rules as posted have been the agreement since it started.  BotS didn't participate in the Dozekar rotation for over a year until we got kind of bored.  We had nothing to say (nor should we have) on the agreement for the Dozekar rotation but I did see it take place.  In the end, we did get on rotation and we didn't ask for a reconsideration of terms because it seemed fair to us.<br>
<br>
The reason the named have been being killed was out of ignorance (not being offensive) of the agreement.  My guess is that none of those guilds bothered to ask anyone if there was even an agreement on them, much less what the agreement was.  The named have been disappearing with little/no explanation for a while and it was only recently when people started finding out which guilds were killing the named.  Now, some folks were brought into a discussion recently and everyone realized that the problem was a lack of information (the rotation guilds didn't provide it in a public forum before now and assumed other guilds would ask an existing rotation guild about it like everyone else had until now) and that is being corrected - the naming of the rotation being changed by request to more accurrately reflect the terms of the agreement and the posting of the agreement itself.<br>
