<br>
Killing the drakes yields NO loot except quest items.<br>
<br>
I think only one quest requires 4 Tears from Dozekar where all the rest require a combination there of.<br>
<br>
Logically, to make Dozekar worth while to kill, you need to kill the named drakes along with him, hence how it was decided it was a package deal.  Even after the advent of the random spawn timers (Blah), the guilds on the rotation were able to keep it as a package deal for the most part.<br>
<br>
There was an occasional accidental killing from time to time of the named drakes by HOT farming guilds, but it was worked out.  To keep all this intact isn't that difficult, it's just asking the people that are there to be a little more careful.<br>
<br>
I know the pull routes inside the HoT like the back of my hand...I should after all this time, and I can say for a fact, you can farm the left side of the Dozekar room (facing in from the door) without ever touching a named Drake.  They all spawn behind and to the right of the room.  Unless you fight to the exit, you can avoid ever killing the named drakes this way. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthaldin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thaldin</A> at: 9/16/02 3:27:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujurrasicepoch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jurrasic Epoch</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FK Rep</span><br>  Posts: 474<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 6:41:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thegeekhost.com/gravedirt/friend.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> Thank you for replying Emil, but I don't believe that it DOES answer my question.<br>
<br>
Though the named and Dozekar ARE linked in that the two 'parts' from each complete the quests, they are NOT the same mob.  <br>
<br>
While the initial founders of the rotation decided to make them a package deal, it does not have to be this way. <br>
<br>
Otherwise you could make the claim that all VP medallion mobs and ground spawns are part of the Trakanon rotation and must never be killed by non Trakanon guilds or rot guilds not currently up for Trakanon.<br>
<br>
The question was IF the majority of Dozekar rotation guilds didn't care to check HoT every day for their named to spawn and decided that it was just as easy to 'take em when you want em' (and there have been times that Doze is killed multiple times before the named are touched) does the majority rule in this decision to remove the named from the rotation? why or why not?<br>
<br>
Again please keep in mind that this is hypothetical, and FK as a Dozekar rotation guild makes no position for or against a change at this time, but it should be hashed out as I have a funny feeling that this sort of issue may well come up in the future with 'linked' mobs in PoP, as well as with Doze now.<br>
